prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Primaily consists of grant administration records as well as records created and mantained by the Grants Management Office.
Contains administrative records, budgets, reports, proposals and planning documents, meeting records, program plans and reviews, surveys and briefing books.

Subjects focus primarily on Women's Health including the activities of Commonwealth Fund Commission on Women's Health, the Commonwealth Fund Women's Health Surveys and health care and medicare reform.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Commonwealth Fund archive was donated to RAC in 1985. Accretions to the collection continue on an ongoing basis. This material was transferred to the Archive Center in 2002.
